</i></p><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-14_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Health and Social Care (HSC) Northern Ireland is a crucial entity responsible for delivering integrated health and social care services to the population of Northern Ireland. The organisation plays a pivotal role in ensuring the well-being of citizens through comprehensive healthcare and social support systems. In this blog, Dr Richard Dune explores the key functions of HSC Northern Ireland, highlights essential statistics, defines critical terms, and outlines best practices for implementing relevant legislation and regulations. </span>
